<TITLE> Witnesses begin testifying in Ramna twin cases, finally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)Eight years into the bloody bombing at the Ramna Batamul during Bangla New Year celebrations, a Dhaka court on Sunday started recording statement of the witnesses. The plaintiff of the case, sub-inspector Amal Chandra Dey , former officer in charge of Babupura Police Station, testified before Dhaka Metropolitan Sessions Judge's Court from 11:30am to 3:15pm. The court has fixed May 17-19 for recording statement of the witnesses in two separate cases filed with the court on the same incident. Five accused Mufti Abdul Hannan , Mufti Abdur Rouf Abu Taher, Arif Hasan and Shahadat Ullah Jewel who are already in jail appeared before the court . The eight other accused are absconding. Charges of the twin cases, for murder and bombing, were framed at noon by Dhaka metropolitan sessions judge ANN Bashirullah. All the accused pleaded not guilty to the charges. Six dates were fixed by the judge to take statement of the witnesses for the two cases  May 3, 4 and 5 for the murder case and April 28, 29 and 30 for the bombing case. Earlier, charges could not be framed as the prosecution appealed for time. CID inspector Abu Hena Mohammad Yusuf filed two charge sheets for murder and bombing cases on Nov 30 last year naming 14 accused and 84 witnesses. Five of the accused are in jail, one on bail and eight are at large
